An adhesive composition comprises polythene and a minor proportion of ammonium sulphamate and, optionally, a chlorinated paraffin, e.g. chlorinated paraffin wax. The components may be blended on heated rolls or in a mixer. Laminated or coated articles may be made by placing a layer of the composition, e.g. in powder, dust, sheet, tape or gasket form, on the surface or between lamin , e.g. of glass, metal, ceramic ware, wood, fibre or plastic and heating at 130-220 DEG C. under a pressure of 0 to 2000 lbs./sq. in.